        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 2:37PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 236 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Brevard, or near B.R. Parkway-Mount Pisgah To The Nc
Arboretum, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mills River, Fletcher, Etowah, B.R. Parkway-Mount Pisgah To The Nc
Arboretum, Asheville Airport, Mount Pisgah, Mountain Home, Arden,
Avery Creek, and Forge Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
